Remarks on ecology, biology and conservation. It is a still-water adapted species, invasive in lakes Skadar, Ohrid and lakes of Adriatic drainages of Croatia , and low course of rivers. Spawning takes place between April and May (
Mačrovcić et al ., 2006
). Its conservation status is of “Low Concern” according to IUCN ( 2013 ) red list.
